{"7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140":{"concepts":["AgentMemory hooks (SessionStart, UserPromptSubmit, PreToolUse) trigger context injection","Dual compression paths: synthetic (zero-LLM, always available) vs LLM-powered (AUTO_COMPRESS optional)","Memory hierarchy: raw observations â†’ synthetic compression/indexing â†’ LLM consolidation â†’ durable lessons/memories","Context injection multi-stage filtering: project-scoped priority, importance thresholds, token budgeting","Consolidation pipeline: requires 3+ observations sharing concept, groups by concept, caps LLM calls at 10/run","Memory tab displays consolidated memories from crystallize/consolidate/reflect; timeline/sessions/activity tabs show raw observations","Lesson sources: manual (user-created), crystal (crystallize function), consolidation (consolidate function)","Embedding model: local Xenova/transformers (all-MiniLM or equivalent) for zero-API dependency vector search","BM25 and vector search are pure statisticalâ€”no model inference or API calls during retrieval","Observation persistence: state_store.db filesystem storage + REST API access independent of LLM provider"],"createdAt":"2026-06-27T20:36:27.306Z","filesModified":["~/.agentmemory/.env","~/.zshrc","~/.zshrc.bak-20260627-125006","/Users/gwang/github_repo/agentmemory/src/config.ts","/Users/gwang/github_repo/agentmemory/src/triggers/api.ts","/Users/gwang/github_repo/agentmemory/src/functions/consolidate.ts","/Users/gwang/github_repo/agentmemory/src/functions/context.ts","/Users/gwang/github_repo/agentmemory/src/functions/enrich.ts","/Users/gwang/github_repo/agentmemory/src/functions/compress-synthetic.ts","/Users/gwang/github_repo/agentmemory/src/functions/crystallize.ts","/Users/gwang/github_repo/agentmemory/src/functions/lessons.ts","/Users/gwang/github_repo/agentmemory/src/mcp/tools-registry.ts","/Users/gwang/Develop/accounting-firm/data/state_store.db/"],"keyDecisions":["Migrated ANTHROPIC_API_KEY from ~/.zshrc shell config to ~/.agentmemory/.env for centralized secrets management and environment isolation","Confirmed retrieval/injection paths are independent of LLM providerâ€”BM25 and local embeddings enable memory recall without external API calls","Validated that observations persist in state_store.db regardless of AUTO_COMPRESS or LLM availability; compression pipeline is optional enhancement","Identified lesson/memory creation requires explicit API calls (POST /agentmemory/lessons, /memories, /consolidate) or manual crystallize/reflect functionsâ€”no automatic creation on hook triggers"],"narrative":"The session focused on configuring an Anthropic API key for the AgentMemory system and investigating why the dashboard Memories tab appeared empty despite storing 750+ observations. Key findings: observations are stored in a state database and indexed locally (no LLM required), but consolidation into durable memories requires an LLM provider for the summarize function. The user configured their API key from console.anthropic.com into ~/.agentmemory/.env, enabling the LLM-backed consolidation pipeline. Investigation revealed the memory system uses dual paths: synthetic compression (zero-LLM, always available) for indexing and search, and optional LLM compression (AUTO_COMPRESS) for richer summaries. The Memories tab displays consolidated memories created via the consolidate/crystallize/reflect pipelines, distinct from raw observations stored in the state database.","observationCount":123,"project":"agentmemory","sessionId":"7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140","title":"AgentMemory API Configuration and Memory Consolidation Debugging"},"92617014-5d50-4f04-ba98-da6ee9fa198d":{"concepts":["HTTP 429 rate limiting","Email verification code resend","HttpErrorResponse status code handling","i18n translation management","Angular error handling in async operations"],"createdAt":"2026-06-27T19:35:21.477Z","filesModified":["frontend/src/app/features/auth/login-email-code/login-email-code.component.ts","frontend/public/i18n/public/en.json","frontend/public/i18n/public/zh.json"],"keyDecisions":["Detect HTTP 429 status code in frontend resendCode() method to distinguish rate-limit errors from other failures, providing specific user feedback about the 60-second cooldown requirement","Add dedicated translation keys for both generic resend errors and cooldown-specific errors to support proper i18n across language variants","Implement error handling in component using HttpErrorResponse to access status codes from failed HTTP requests"],"narrative":"Fixed email verification code resend functionality to properly handle rate-limiting. When users attempt to resend a verification code within 60 seconds, the backend returns HTTP 429, which the frontend now detects and displays a user-friendly cooldown message instead of a generic error. Added error handling in the login-email-code component's resendCode() method, implemented HTTP 429 status detection with HttpErrorResponse, and added localized error messages in both English and Chinese translation files.","observationCount":71,"project":"accounting-firm","sessionId":"92617014-5d50-4f04-ba98-da6ee9fa198d","title":"Email Verification Code Resend Rate-Limit Handling"},"bc74e163-6da3-4a1d-89a8-740a6cb0c102":{"concepts":["activeEngagementStatus: Computed server-side field on ClientDto representing each client's most recent non-COMPLETED tax year engagement state for workflow visibility","Spring Data JPA derived queries: findFirstByClientIdAndStatusNotOrderByTaxYearDesc for efficient single engagement fetch without additional service logic","Workflow state column: New admin client list table column displaying engagement status badges with filter and deep-link action button per row","Per-row workflow action: Button added to each client row navigating to `/admin/clients/:id/workflow` for consolidated access","Navigation consolidation: Removal of standalone /admin/workflow nav link in favor of per-client workflow buttons integrated into client management","OpenSpec superpowers-driven schema: Requirements â†’ Proposal â†’ Specs â†’ Design â†’ Tasks â†’ Contracts â†’ Evaluation workflow with external evaluator verification","Test-driven development (TDD): RED failing tests â†’ GREEN implementation â†’ evaluator verification cycle enforced for both backend and frontend","External evaluator subagent: Skeptical assessment of implementation contracts with >80 threshold score requirement","E2E workflow validation: Playwright tests covering navbar absence, column rendering, filter persistence, button navigation, and workflow action accessibility","Test mock propagation: Updated ClientDto instantiations across messaging, documents, and threads test files for interface consistency","Backend-frontend contract alignment: ClientDto interface specification as contract boundary between implementation groups"],"createdAt":"2026-06-27T21:21:07.246Z","filesModified":["openspec/changes/workflow-to-client-mgmt/.openspec.yaml","openspec/changes/workflow-to-client-mgmt/requirements.md","openspec/changes/workflow-to-client-mgmt/proposal.md","openspec/changes/workflow-to-client-mgmt/specs/admin-workflow-ui/spec.md","openspec/changes/workflow-to-client-mgmt/specs/client-management/spec.md","openspec/changes/workflow-to-client-mgmt/design.md","openspec/changes/workflow-to-client-mgmt/tasks.md","openspec/changes/workflow-to-client-mgmt/contracts/group-1.md","openspec/changes/workflow-to-client-mgmt/contracts/group-2.md","openspec/changes/workflow-to-client-mgmt/eval-log.md","backend/src/main/java/com/gwhaitech/accountingfirm/client/domain/ClientEngagementRepository.java","backend/src/main/java/com/gwhaitech/accountingfirm/client/dto/ClientDto.java","backend/src/main/java/com/gwhaitech/accountingfirm/client/service/ClientService.java","backend/src/test/java/com/gwhaitech/accountingfirm/client/service/ClientServiceTest.java","backend/src/test/java/com/gwhaitech/accountingfirm/client/controller/ClientControllerTest.java","backend/src/test/java/com/gwhaitech/accountingfirm/messaging/controller/AdminMessageControllerTest.java","backend/src/test/java/com/gwhaitech/accountingfirm/client/controller/DocumentControllerTest.java","frontend/src/app/core/models/client.model.ts","frontend/src/app/features/admin/clients/admin-clients.component.ts","frontend/src/app/features/admin/clients/admin-clients.component.html","frontend/src/app/features/admin/clients/admin-clients.component.spec.ts","frontend/src/app/shared/navbar/navbar.component.html","frontend/src/app/shared/navbar/navbar.component.spec.ts","frontend/src/app/features/admin/client-messages/admin-client-thread-view.component.spec.ts","frontend/src/app/features/admin/client-messages/admin-client-threads.component.spec.ts","frontend/src/app/features/admin/client-documents/admin-client-documents.component.spec.ts","e2e/workflow-to-client-mgmt.spec.ts","docs/log/2026-06-27.md"],"keyDecisions":["Backend: Used Spring Data derived query `findFirstByClientIdAndStatusNotOrderByTaxYearDesc` with EngagementStatus.COMPLETED filter to fetch most recent active engagement server-side, returning null if no engagements exist or all are COMPLETED.","Frontend: Added activeEngagementStatus as nullable field to ClientDto interface and updated test mocks across messaging, documents, and threads components for consistency.","Navigation: Removed \"Workflow\" nav link entirely from navbar since workflow is now accessible via per-client action button in admin client list.","UI Layout: Placed workflow status column next to Name in client table with colspan adjustment from 5 to 6; added per-row Workflow action button navigating to `/admin/clients/:id/workflow`.","Engagement status representation: Display most recent non-COMPLETED engagement status; show COMPLETED if all engagements finished; null if no engagements exist.","OpenSpec structure: Organized as superpowers-driven schema with all artifacts (requirements, proposal, specs, design, tasks, contracts, eval-log) and three distinct implementation groups evaluated separately.","Testing strategy: Applied TDD (RED â†’ GREEN) for both backend and frontend; created comprehensive E2E suite covering navbar absence, status column rendering, filter persistence, button navigation, and workflow accessibility."],"narrative":"Completed a comprehensive three-group OpenSpec change consolidating workflow management into client list views, eliminating the standalone Workflow nav section. Implemented backend activeEngagementStatus field on ClientDto using Spring Data derived queries to efficiently fetch each client's most recent non-COMPLETED engagement, then integrated a workflow status column into the admin client list with per-row action buttons. Removed the top-level Workflow nav link and created full OpenSpec documentation (requirements, proposal, specs, design, tasks, contracts). All three groups passed external evaluation (99/100 score) with 308 backend tests, 9 new frontend component tests, and 5 E2E tests validating the consolidated UI workflows.","observationCount":1532,"project":"accounting-firm","sessionId":"bc74e163-6da3-4a1d-89a8-740a6cb0c102","title":"Workflow-to-Client-Mgmt: Complete OpenSpec Refactor with Backend/Frontend Integration"},"cbb9884f-4076-4830-8f5d-1ed5a8e58546":{"concepts":["Memory persistence and lesson creation","Confidence scoring in memory systems","Memory decay and reinforcement tracking","User identity management","MCP agent memory tools"],"createdAt":"2026-06-27T20:31:19.671Z","filesModified":[],"keyDecisions":["Used memory_lesson_save tool instead of direct memory_save for explicit lesson creation, allowing for structured persistence with confidence scoring and decay tracking","Tagged the memory entry with \"user-name\" and \"gary\" for improved searchability and contextual retrieval"],"narrative":"The session focused on testing and configuring the AI agent's memory system. A lesson was created to remember the user's name \"Gary\" with high confidence (1.0) and tagged with relevant metadata. The agent successfully used the memory_lesson_save tool to persist this information, demonstrating proper integration with the memory persistence layer. The lesson was assigned a decay rate of 0.05 and source type of \"manual\" for tracking purposes.","observationCount":7,"project":"accounting-firm","sessionId":"cbb9884f-4076-4830-8f5d-1ed5a8e58546","title":"Memory System Setup - User Identity Lesson Created"},"ef220526-7344-435e-b72c-ee4732ba534d":{"concepts":["Claude plugin management system","superpowers plugin","plugin version tracking","Claude configuration directory","project-specific plugin installation"],"createdAt":"2026-06-27T20:46:39.399Z","filesModified":["/Users/gwang/.claude/plugins/installed_plugins.json"],"keyDecisions":["Used Python JSON parsing to extract specific plugin version information from installed_plugins.json, filtering for plugins associated with the accounting-firm project path","Navigated Claude's plugin configuration at ~/.claude/plugins/ rather than the initial assumption of ~/.claude/plugins directory structure"],"narrative":"The user queried the version of the superpowers plugin installed in their Claude environment. The session involved navigating the Claude configuration directory structure to locate plugin metadata, specifically examining the installed_plugins.json file. Through a series of filesystem explorations and JSON parsing, the agent identified that the superpowers plugin (superpowers@claude-plugins-official) was installed and extracted its version information for an accounting-firm project located at /Users/gwang/Develop/accounting-firm.","observationCount":7,"project":"accounting-firm","sessionId":"ef220526-7344-435e-b72c-ee4732ba534d","title":"Investigate Superpowers Plugin Version in Claude Environment"}}␀ł×␀␀Ę˙˙